sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Admin as User / Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller<br/>(manager binary)
    participant DSCICtrl as DSCI Controller<br/>(manager binary)
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller<br/>(e.g., Dashboard)
    participant GWCtrl as Gateway Controller<br/>(manager binary)

    rect rgb(232, 240, 254)
        Note over Admin,CompCtrl: Flow 1: Component Enablement via DSC
        Admin->>K8sAPI: Create/Update DataScienceCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>DSCCtrl: Watch event (DSC CR)
        DSCCtrl->>DSCCtrl: Parse DSC spec → component states
        DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Component CR<br/>(e.g., Dashboard CR)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI->>CompCtrl: Watch event (Component CR)
        CompCtrl->>CompCtrl: Render Kustomize/Helm manifests
        CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Deployments, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, etc.<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Update Component CR status
        DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Aggregate status → DSC status
    end

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant EnvoyF as EnvoyFilter<br/>(ext_authz + Lua)
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth /<br/>OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CompSvc as Component Service<br/>(backend)

    rect rgb(220, 237, 200)
        Note over Client,CompSvc: Flow 2: Gateway Authentication (OAuth/OIDC)
        Client->>Gateway: HTTPS request (443/TCP)<br/>TLS 1.2+ Terminate
        Gateway->>EnvoyF: ext_authz check
        EnvoyF->>AuthProxy: Auth validation (8443/TCP)<br/>HTTPS TLS (service-CA)<br/>Cookie or Bearer token
        alt No valid session
            AuthProxy->>Client: 302 Redirect → OAuth/OIDC login
            Client->>OAuth: OAuth2/OIDC authentication<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP TLS 1.2+
            OAuth-->>Client: Authorization code redirect
            Client->>AuthProxy: /oauth2/callback<br/>with authorization code
            AuthProxy->>OAuth: Exchange code for token<br/>Client credentials
            OAuth-->>AuthProxy: Access token + ID token
            AuthProxy-->>Client: Set session cookie
        end
        AuthProxy-->>EnvoyF: 200 OK (valid session)
        EnvoyF->>EnvoyF: Lua filter: strip OAuth cookies,<br/>set Authorization: Bearer header
        EnvoyF->>CompSvc: Forward request<br/>with Bearer token
        CompSvc-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS response
    end

    participant CloudMgr as Cloud Manager<br/>(cloudmanager binary)
    participant HelmEngine as Helm Chart<br/>Renderer
    participant CertMgr as cert-manager CR
    participant SailOp as Sail/Istio CR
    participant LWSOp as LWS Operator CR

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over Admin,LWSOp: Flow 3: Cloud Manager Dependency Deployment
        Admin->>K8sAPI: Create Cloud CR<br/>(e.g., AWSKubernetesEngine)
        K8sAPI->>CloudMgr: Watch event (Cloud CR)
        CloudMgr->>HelmEngine: BuildHelmCharts<br/>(in-process rendering)
        CloudMgr->>K8sAPI: Create cert-manager Operator CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        CloudMgr->>K8sAPI: Create Sail/Istio Operator CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        CloudMgr->>K8sAPI: Create LWS Operator CR<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        CloudMgr->>K8sAPI: Create Gateway API CRDs<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        CloudMgr->>K8sAPI: Update Cloud CR status
    end
